Package: wasta-multidesktop
Architecture: all
Depends: arc-theme, at, jq, papirus-icon-theme, rename, wasta-app-tweaks, wasta-backgrounds, wasta-core, wasta-resources, wmctrl, xmlstarlet, ${misc:Depends}
Recommends: arc-solid-theme, papirus-folders, wasta-papirus, wasta-vertex-ubuntu
Description: Wasta-Linux MultiDesktop
 Ensures cross-desktop compatibility between different desktop sessions.
 A systemd triggered script runs on login to make necessary adjustments based
 on detected session in comparison to previously detected session.
 .
 Currently only GNOME, Cinnamon, and XFCE are supported.
